climbs.name: This Sport Used to be Free

content.description:
Bouldery, sequential moves from the get-go on just generous enough holds to a small hole/hueco shake. Pull a couple more difficult moves over the bulge using a sweet pocket and some face holds. Easier but slightly suspect rock keeps things interesting to the shared anchor with "Chicks for Free".

It's nice to climb a Maple 5.12- that has a low, bouldery crux instead of the standard pumpy sting at the finish.
content.location: The right-most route on the Free Wall. It's the first route you'll encounter as you approach the wall and has the best belay situation (flat!) of all the routes on the wall.

content.description: The left-most route of the three routes on the Free Wall. Pull on to the rock using flakes and knobs and follow a juggy flake system up to its terminus. Face climb past another bolt or two to the anchor.
content.protection: Four bolts to a two bolt anchor.
content.location: Left-most route on the wall. Scramble up the short slope to find the start.

content.description: Tough, fingery moves on tiny holds off the ground up a vertical section of rock. About halfway up the angle backs off a bit and the holds improve.
content.protection: 6 bolts to a two bolt anchor.
content.location: Center route of the three routes on the Free Wall.
